The article discusses the ongoing issue of gun violence in the United States and calls for immediate action from Congress. It highlights the recent mass shootings and expresses condolences for the victims and their families. The author emphasizes the need for common-sense gun law reforms such as background checks on all gun sales, banning assault weapons and high-capacity magazines, closing the boyfriend loophole, requiring safe storage of guns, and eliminating immunity for gun manufacturers. The article concludes by stating that these steps could be taken right now to save lives and address the epidemic of gun violence in American communities.